IBADAN-IN search of a lasting solution to the security challenges confronting the south-west states, Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State will on Monday host the Inspector-General of Police, Mr Mohammed Adamu, service chiefs and five other south-west states governors in Ibadan. The meeting tagged: “South-West Geopolitical Zone Security Summit” was convened by the Inspector-General of Police to unveil his security agenda for the south-west states and to discuss issues and strategies to be adopted in addressing the security challenges in the geopolitical zone. Also read: Taraba Killings: Police forensic experts perform autopsy of murdered IRT operatives According to a statement signed by the Special Assistant on Print Media to the Oyo State Governor, Mr Moses Alao, the meeting, which will be held at the International Conference Centre, University of Ibadan, is expected to also have in attendance foremost royal fathers, elder statesmen, leaders of socio-cultural groups and other key stakeholders in the south-west zone. The event is coming up few days to the unveiling of new security architecture for Oyo State by Governor Makinde and on the heels of a similar security summit held in June by governours of the south-west through the Development Agenda for Western Nigeria (DAWN) Commission. Vanguard GOVERNORS from the South West geo-political zone will converge in Ibadan, Oyo State to address the security challenges confronting the region. June 24, 2019 In "News" CHAIRMAN of the South West Governor’s Forum and Ondo State governor, Mr. Rotimi Akeredolu, yesterday, assured that the proposed security summit will put an end to the activities of marauding herdsmen and address the insecurity challenges in the region. June 19, 2019 In "News" KATSINA — The North-West Governors and Inspector General of Police, IGP Mohammed Adamu, yesterday, stormed Katsina State for a crucial meeting over spate of insecurity, including kidnapping and other violent crimes bedeviling the region. August 2, 2019 In "News"